{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
I[A]deas that you'll never find[Em]
All the inventors could never design[D]
The buil[A]dings that you put up[Em]
Japan and China all lit up[D]
The [A]sign that I couldn't read[Em]
Or a light that I couldn't see[D]
Some [A]things you have to believe[Em]
But others are puzzles, puzzling me[D]
{end_of_verse}


